Sending warm wishes of central heating to the people of the Baltic nation of Latvia this week as the country heads into the week forecast to be its coldest week of 2019. Temperatures in the inland northeast region of the country (pictured) are expected to reach as low as -25 Celsius (-13 Fahrenheit).

This forecast comes on the heels of last week’s announcement that the country’s current outbreak of influenza has officially reached the level of being designated an epidemic, with more than 75 residents per 100,000 being affected in the capital city of Riga. The Disease Prevention Control Centre has recommended that affected individuals remain at home and wash their hands regularly - and recommends that all residents consider an influenza vaccination to curb the spread of the infection.

caption: In America, the chances of dying from cervical cancer is 2.3 out of 100,000. The chances of getting an autoimmune disease from this vaccine are 2.3 out of 100. Your chances of getting autoimmune disease from this vaccine are 1000 time greater than getting cervical cancer. Nobody in the world who has any concern for their little girl would ever give them this vaccine unless they’re innocently uninformed. The HPV vaccine has killed and injured many girls! It’s loaded with aluminum (see previous posts about injected aluminum). Furthermore, cervical cancer rates in dozens of countries have risen since the introduction of the HPV vaccine, and Pap smear tests have dropped. When Pap smear tests were routinely conducted, cancer rates remained low. “It takes a long time to affirm preventative action really protects. But the failure of this supposed protection can sometimes be very quickly obvious. To prove that the titanic was truly unsinkable would have required decades of navigation on the most dangerous seas of the world. Demonstrating that it wasn’t, took only a few hours. This Titanic demonstration is unfortunately reproduced by the Gardasil vaccination. Evidence that vaccination increases the risk of invasive cancer can be rapid, if the vaccine changes the natural history of cancer by accelerating it. The analysis of trends in the incidence of invasive cervical cancer published in official statistics registers was studied in the first and most fully vaccinated countries. Unfortunately, it’s the case for HPV vaccines” - Dr. Nicole Delepine, a surgeon and oncologist from France. There are so many points to make it’s stupid......Just recently 5 Yale professors backed out of a conference with Kennedy....There will never be an open debate because that’s how obvious it is. One day people are going to realize what’s been going on this whole time and will have to reflect on why we character assassinated those who brought facts that were benefiting us all. Even if you don’t have kids YOU should be worried. This is our first amendment that they’re trying to take away. We will no longer have Medical Freedom if they decide to mandate vaccines.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is serious y’all!! It will no longer be a Pro/Anti vaxx decision anymore, because everyone will be FORCED. They talked about how to enforce it for adults. Denying adults their ability to renew their driver's license, professional licenses, and hunting/fishing license was suggested.⁣⁣

Believe it or not but this bill IS and WILL affect EVERY SINGLE AMERICAN FAMILY not just the Anti or Ex Vax Families. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When there is a risk, there must ALWAYS be a choice. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is a huge slippery slope, what could come next? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s how we can all help:⁣⁣

#rp #POPULATIONCONTROL 
For several years the #Israeli #government was forcibly administering #birthcontrol to a segment of its minority population with #doctors injecting #Ethiopian #Jewish women against their will with a contraceptive, #DepoProvera. “But it wasn’t until this January that a government official finally acknowledged it. One investigative journalist who interviewed thirty five Ethiopian #immigrants found that they were being intimidated and threatened into taking the shots while being told that they were merely inoculations. Many speculate that it was all part of a deliberate attempt to restrict an expanding minority

Ethiopian women have told #RT that Israeli #medics forced them to take the controversial Depo-Provera birth control #vaccination without explaining the severe #sideeffects of the #drug, which can leave a woman unable to become #pregnant for up to two years.

The birth control vaccination was reportedly a requirement for the women to immigrate to #Israel: “They told me if you don't take the shot, we won't give you a ticket, so I took the shot, but I didn't know that it would prevent pregnancies. I didn’t know,” one woman told RT correspondent Paula Slier.

The gruesome side effects of Depo-Provera are so severe that the drug is not recommended for most patients. “We are talking about a contraception that has heavy #medical and #mental effects – period irregularities, #vaginal bleeding, osteoporosis, alongside mental side effects like #depression, #moodswings, #rage and more,” said Sharon Eliyahu-Chai of the Association for Civil Rights in Israel.

caption: Y’all already know where I stand but in case you haven’t heard me say it lately... VACCINATE YO KIDS!!! “But if I give Johnny the flu shot he’ll get the flu.” Possibly, but it won’t be nearly as bad of a case as it would be if Johnny didn’t get vaccinated. A quick poke of the needle is much better than watching your children die of fatal diseases. Not to mention if they ever need an organ transplant, they can be denied due to the fact that they’re not vaccinated. Vaccinations don’t just protect your child, but they protect everyone around them as well. That’s why parents get the whooping cough vaccine while expecting a baby so that their baby is protected, even though he/she is too young to receive the vaccine. Some people can’t have certain vaccines due to health problems. The fact that you are safe from certain diseases lessens their chance of catching one. Rant over...resume your regularly scheduled Friday. #vaccines #vaccination #vaccinateyourkids

*Vaccine* "This cancer doesn't have a magic bullet solution. Anything you can do to minimize the chance of relapse is a good idea. There is no way to know which treatments will work for each child." Chilling words from one of Arli's oncologists.

I've heard this before. In every child with this disease, Neuroblastoma is different. 
As I type this, there are teams of doctors trying to innovate personalized Neuroblastoma treatments. Unfortunately, we're just not there yet.

Parents of Neuroblastoma patients must contend with a myriad of treatment options, clinical trials, their child's individual expression of the disease, and the advice of countless physicians. There is no one-size-fits-all approach. 
My husband and I have decided to seek additional options in Arli's care. 
We are going to participate in a clinical trial of a Neuroblastoma vaccine. If successful, this vaccine would help Arli's body kill Neuroblastoma cells that may develop down the road.

You can read more about the clinical trial here: https://www.mskcc.org/cancer-care/clinical-trials/05-075

This Tuesday, Arli and I will fly to New York. At Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center, Arli will receive injections with little, if any, side effects. We are so excited!

In preparation for our trip, Arli's body was scanned. 
Scans for children as young as Arli are done under sedation to help them remain still.

Arli had a cold on the day of our appointment, so she was deemed unfit for sedation. We were about to be turned away, when my brave five-year-old asked, "Can I try? I will hold very still!" "We don't even have a working television for you to look at." The nurse answered.

I could understand the imaging team's hesitation. They usually don't let kids under eight attempt an MRI awake "It's OK!" Arli chimed with confidence.

Who could say no to that?

I couldn't believe the self-control and determination Arli had. My five-year-old was in the tube for over an hour and didn't move!

We celebrated with a fabulous piece of lemon curd stuffed french toast, which was smothered in blueberry sauce.

Over the last 17 years, I’ve read hundreds of medical journal articles on the problems associated with vaccines. I have written and spoken about vaccine contaminants – stray viruses, #aluminum, #mercury, polysorbate 80, animal cells, and so on. I have often wondered “What else is coming through that needle?” This article, “New Quality-Control Investigations on Vaccines: Micro and Nano-contamination” published on January 23, 2017, in the peer-reviewed journal, the International Journal of Vaccines & Vaccination absolutely blew me away.

Here is a snapshot from this must-read, full-text article:

A team of scientists in Italy decided to examine batches of vaccines, looking for contaminants not listed as ingredients. 44 types of vaccines manufactured in #Italy and #France were analyzed using an Environmental Electron Scanning Microscope. This method was chosen because the matter can be separated into either organic debris (called aggregates) or inorganic debris (called clusters). The identified particles were counted three times by three different operators, with an error rate of less than 10%. They found inorganic contaminants in every single one.

The presence of micro- and nanosized particulate matter, composed of inorganic chemicals, metals and combination elements whose presence is inexplicable.

The particles are foreign bodies, and can produce a chronic inflammatory reaction because the particles cannot be degraded. The tiny #nanoparticles can enter the cell nuclei and interact with cellular DNA.

The inorganic particles are neither biocompatible nor biodegradable, that means they are biopersistent. They can induce immediate effects or the effects may be delayed for a long time after administration.

Indentifying Aluminum and NaCl is obvious because they are commonly used in vaccines and they are declared components, but the other materials are not supposed to be in vaccines or in any other injectable drug. :raised_hand_medium-dark_skin_tone:More in comments:backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-dark_skin_tone:#SB277 #SB279 #SB217 #MandatoryVaccines #PopulationControl #AntiVax

The World Health Organization most recently released their “Ten threats to global health in 2019”. :globe_showing_Americas::globe_showing_Americas::globe_showing_Americas: Two of them in particular really caught my attention: vaccine hesitancy and dengue. :syringe:While I won’t go into why vaccine hesitancy, also known as the anti-vax movement, is a HUGE problem, here are some quick Dengue facts! (Swipe for the structure of Dengue)

Dengue is a viral infection transmitted through Aedes aegypti mosquito bites. Mostly found in  Asia and Latin America, this infection can hemorrhagic fever. This can lead to severe bleeding and death. According to the WHO there are about 390 million infections worldwide each year!

What makes this virus so hard to tackle is the fact that dengue virus undergoes antibody dependent enhancement of disease. There are 4 different types of dengue. When someone is infected the first time, their body’s immune system responds and produces antibodies against that type of dengue. But when they are infected a second time, those antibodies from the first time make the second viral infection more severe!

Check out the link in my bio to the full WHO article! (First image credit from WHO)

During the 1990's, the U.S. switched from whole-cell pertussis vaccine (in the diphtheria, tetanus, and whole-cell pertussis combination vaccine DTwP) to combined acelluar pertussis (DTaP) vaccines.
•
The study, “Comparative Effectiveness of Acellular Versus Whole-Cell Pertussis Vaccines in Teenagers,” in the June 2013 issue of Pediatrics looked at individuals born between 1994 and 1999 who received four pertussis-containing vaccines in the first two years of life. Some individuals received DTwP, and others received DTaP. The authors found that during a 2009 and 2010 pertussis outbreak, those teenagers who received DTaP had a six times higher risk of contracting pertussis due to waning immunity compared to those who received DTwP.

So this elderly #nurse was giving #BabyC the 10-week vaccine.  Penta 5in1 vaccine is usually given on the left leg and it's the more powerful injection. There was blood on the site and the she pressed it sooo hard.  I was surprised but didn't question her because I felt she knew what she was doing, even though the instruction from the nurses the last time she was immunized, was that the injection site should be left alone without rubbing. 
All we did was gently hold the cotton wool dipped in methylated spirit over the site.

So you can imagine the surprise when the swelling on the injection  site refused to go down after one week. In fact 9 days after the vaccine, I noticed a redness and warmth on the swollen site. 
We called the #health centre and were told to bring her in immediately. 
According to the nurse, #thankfully, the site wasn't fully inflamed yet because there was no pain. It needed to be managed naturally, she said. No antibiotics, simply a cold piece of cloth permanently on the site to prevent the bacteria from growing. 
This meant we needed to keep changing the cloth whenever it went warm. This was on Thursday.  I did it till Saturday...and then till Monday. Oh my! It was a lot of work. In fact, I stayed awake because of that. I participated in #TE13 while staying awake to change the cloth on her.

By Monday, the inflammation had gone, just a blistered looking portion of her skin which we were told to apply #sheabutter on.

The continuous cold cloth on her skin didn't come with its own issue. Now we're dealing with cold symptoms. Thank God she's getting better.

Of course, the nurse made a mistake in the administration of the vaccine and she's lucky I didn't meet her on that day. I got apologies from the senior nurse. 
I'm thankful it wasn't more than what we experienced. 
Please ask questions if you're not sure!

In response to a recent controversial blog I posted called “Media Left Out Horrifying Facts about Measles Shot,” Joanne, a nurse, emailed me. She wrote: “As a school nurse against immunizations, you can imagine the war I am in right now.” If anyone knows a thing or two about administering medicine, it’s Joanne. I’ve been designing and making it for over twenty years, but I’ve never been in a clinical setting to witness first hand the results of mass use.  Joanne is currently in her 9th year working as a school nurse and prior to that, worked as a public health nurse and did substitute school nursing.

She sees firsthand what goes on in schools, while observing the complete lack of common sense among parents who are uninformed about vaccines.

I asked Joanne if I could interview her, and she generously agreed to share some details about her experiences as a school nurse. What follows is an uncensored, no-holds-barred interview with Joanne on how vaccines have wreaked havoc in her schools and why she is AGAINST mandatory vaccination. 
TPC #1: First off, why did you initially choose to work in the field of school nursing?
Joanne: I was looking for a change; I had been working in OB/gyn in a clinical setting, and needed a change. School nursing allows me to work more autonomously.

TPC #2: What has been the greatest reward in working as a school nurse?
Joanne: My greatest reward is helping others with their health. I am a big advocate of preventive health, educating others and seeking natural solutions. It is very rewarding when someone comes back to me to tell me something I suggested worked for them.

caption:
#Repost @nbnmothers with @get_repost
・・・
I'm sure youve all seen the fear mongering floating around about the big bad measles & I'm like :astonished_face: Because truth is, theres no outbreak. CDC : "There were recent media reports misinterpreting CDC data. The number of cases reported in 2018, is similar to recent years and in expected range." People still ask am I scared of my children getting the measles virus? Nope! But, I am scared of the MMR vaccine ; A vaccine that hasn’t been proven safe nor effective & is well known for killing children or leaving them with neurological disorders. Well Isnt measles deadly? Not in this country, or any country whose population is overall healthy. If you understand measles, you wouldn't fear it. The risk of fatality is 1 in many thousands, & we have not had a measles death here in well over 10yrs. Measles are only a threat in underdeveloped countries, not here in the U.S. Between 1900-1963, the mortality rate of measles dropped from 13.3 per 100,00 to 0.2 per 100,000 in the population, due to advancements in living conditions, nutrition & healthcare. Thats a 98% decline ... PRIOR to the introduction of the measles vaccine. The MMR vaccine is what we should fear, there have been 108 deaths in the last 10 yrs (source : VAERS database). As of March 31, 2018, there have been more than 89,355 reports of measles vaccine reactions, hospitalizations, injuries & deaths following the vaccine. These reports were made to VAERS. 445 deaths, 6,196 hospitalizations & 1,657 related disabilities. And over 60% of those adverse events occured in children three years old & under. Your MMR vaccine, it sheds, for up to 6 weeks, so if there were ever to be any cases of measles here in the U.S, it doesn't take a genius or a doctor to figure out who is spreading what. The CDC lists the clinical definition for measles as “an illness characterized by a generalized rash lasting ≥3 days, a temperature of ≥101°F [≥38.3°C], and cough, coryza, and/or conjunctivitis.” So, a rash, cough, & fever is how measles typically presents itself. Measles confers lifelong immunity, something a vaccine can never give you.
#MeaslesShmeasles #DontBeScurred
#EducateBeforeYouVaccinate

The #Alabama Department of Public Health has confirmed that an outbreak of pertussis – also known as whooping cough – in the state was caused by children recently vaccinated against the contagious illness.

The number of people with confirmed #whoopingcough has risen to 19 in an outbreak linked to local schools in #ChambersCounty, where it spread from recently #vaccinated to children to adults.

The Alabama Department of Public Health began investigating the outbreak earlier this month after 6 students came down with the highly-contagious illness. All 19 of the infected adults and children in Chambers County with whooping cough received the #pertussisvaccination.

AL.com reports: Dr. Karen Landers, assistant state health officer, said the #pertussisvaccine is not 100 percent effective. Infants receive several doses during their first year of life, and boosters in early and late childhood. Doctors also recommend pertussis vaccines to pregnant women and unvaccinated adults. :face_with_tears_of_joy::face_with_tears_of_joy::backhand_index_pointing_right_medium_skin_tone::backhand_index_pointing_right_medium_skin_tone:However despite the recent outbreak of potentially deadly pertussis caused by the pertussis vaccine, Landers said the best way to protect babies is still to vaccinate them and ensure all adult caretakers have also received vaccinations. “I would advise any parent – first of all, you want to make sure your child is up-to-date on her vaccines,” Landers said. “We want mothers to be vaccinated during pregnancy. We want children to receive the vaccine on time. caption:
How Did We End Up Like This?
:thinking_face::thinking_face::thinking_face:
Sterilization101
The End

Why is the CDC Ignoring Explosion of Recorded HPV Vaccine Injuries, as Other Countries Move to Take Protective Action?

The HPV vaccine is NOT harmless like it is being promoted and has not been proven to actually prevent cervical cancer

The HPV vaccine only protects against TWO strains of HPV associated with cancer but there are MORE THAN 100 different strains of HPV in all.

Dr. Diane Harper, one of the lead researchers for Gardasil blew the whistle on the vaccine, saying the available data suggests the HPV vaccine's protective effects do not last beyond five years.

The VAERS database continues to swell with reports of autoimmune disorders contracted after receiving the HPV vaccine. These side effects now include 137 reports of cervical dysplasia, and 41 reports of cervical cancer.

HPV infection clears up on its own within two years in 90 percent of all cases. It rarely leads to cervical cancer unless the infection becomes chronic and leads to cervical changes that remain untreated. 
Routine pap smear testing can identify chronic HPV infection and may provide greater protection against development of cervical cancer than reliance on an HPV vaccine that has not been adequately proven to be safe or effective.

The federal government's Vaccine Adverse Events Reporting System (VAERS) has received over 9,000 reports of problems since the vaccine's introduction in 2006, which include at least 28 spontaneous abortions, and 27 deaths. 
Is it possible that Gardasil’s cry to fame, ‘One Less’, is turning out to be nothing but a sick, ironic play on words? 
Anti-Fertility Vaccines 
The World Health Organization (WHO) and its subsidiaries have been actively researching and funding the development of contraceptive / anti-fertility vaccines that prevent full-term pregnancies to take place, for over 20 years. There’s even a Task Force on Birth Control Vaccines of the WHO!

caption:
8 ‪#‎Tips‬ For ‪#‎Parents‬ to Help #Kids Get Back to ‪#‎School‬ from kids.gov
‪#‎parenting‬

1. #Stress: Help your child with time management skills to get #homework done.

2. #Mobile devices: Help your teen learn online safety tips and how to recognize online #stalkers.

3. #Bullying: Learn the warning signs and ways to address the situation at school or #online.

4. #Safety: Communicate with your #children about safety rules on the #bus.

5. #Healthy #Eating: Learn the signs of possible eating #disorders among teenagers.

6. #Sleep: Pre-school-aged children need 11 to 12 hours of sleep; school-aged children need at least ten hours a night; and teens need about nine to ten hours.

7. School Emergencies: Check with your child's school administrator and learn what type of security plan and emergency alert system it uses

8. #Vaccines: Your state board of education or local school district may have a list of required shots before your child can attend school.

#Read more at the link in our profile!

#Repost @vaccinetruth with @get_repost
・・・
Measles! There's no such thing as an illness or disease that doesn't have sometimes associated complications and death - even the common cold. Yet, we wouldn't call the #commoncold anything other than benign. In this practice, #measles is considered as a relatively mild and inevitable #childhood ailment that is best encountered any time from 3 to 7 years of age. As of March 31, 2018, there have been more than 89,355 reports of measles vaccine reactions, hospitalizations, injuries and deaths following measles #vaccinations made to the federal Vaccine Adverse Events Reporting System (VAERS), including 445 related deaths, 6,196 hospitalizations, and 1,657 related disabilities. Over 60% of those adverse events occurred in children three years old and under. 
Learn the facts about measles: https://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/measles/dis/

caption:
Measles :face_with_thermometer:
.
Last year, by August, there were around 9000 cases of Measles reported. This year they are 41000.
.
But meanwhile, the numbers of measles infections are decreasing in the rest of the world. There were literary 2 times more cases of Measles in Europe than Africa this year until now :exploding_head:
.
Measles is THE MOST contagious virus known. It likes to hang out in one’s trachea, much closer to the respiratory exit than other viruses :sneezing_face: So when a person sneezes or coughs, the virus gets projected, like it’s jumping on a trampoline :speaking_head:
.
 It really spreads like :fire:wildfire:fire: : one person with measles, can infect an average of 90 more people (if they’re not immune to it).
.
At first it causes fevers :face_with_thermometer:, runny :nose_medium-light_skin_tone::droplet:, red eyes :eyes: , and tiny white spots in the mouth :mouth:. After, a big rash develops on the skin that spreads through the whole body. In some cases (30%), it can lead to more severe complications and even death :dizzy_face: Not pleasant, right?
.
Although you may think measles is a thing of the past and no one dies of this anymore, that is not true. Still, 250 people die due to this infection every day and in europe the number of deaths per year is increasing. But these deaths could be avoided by a simple vaccine :syringe:
.
The vaccine is composed by weakened measles virus, which is sufficient to activate your immune system to make antibodies against the virus, but not enough to make you sick. These antibodies join a “database” of all antibodies, ready to act in future infections :flexed_biceps_medium-light_skin_tone:
.
So, if you actually get in touch with someone infected, these anti-measles antibodies will quickly recognise the virus and get rid of it :cross_mark:
.
This vaccine is pretty safe and getting it is a matter of public health. Getting these vaccines is a privilege that some don’t have, due to reasons such as economic status, health or location. It is our responsibility to protect the ones who cannot have or do not yet have protection against this disease. May we be able to eradicate Measles soon! :raising_hands_medium-light_skin_tone:
.

caption:
Some serious cousin love :red_heart: By popular request - why lots of parents are getting a chicken pox booster shot for their children :chicken: • In Australia all children get a MMRV vaccine at 18 months- this contains protection against varicella which is chicken pox. A single dose of the chicken pox vaccine prevents 85% of cases of varicella whereas adding a booster dose can provide up to 95% protection. Chicken pox is highly contagious and can have severe complications including pneumonia and a brain infection called encephalitis. Most cases of chicken pox occur in children under 5 years old- Miss S has the second booster dose last year. What many patients don’t realise is that after chicken pox infection the virus lies dormant in spinal nerve roots and it can reactivate with stress/illness/immune issues - and cause shingles. Preventing chicken pox with vaccination is not only in the interests of preventing chicken pox (and it’s complications) but also for preventing shingles :thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone::thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone: That’s the booster dose explained in a nutshell :peanuts: IF you are considering the second dose for your child- you need to pay for the second dose (it’s not government funded) and chat to tour GP about timing this around other vaccines because it is a live vaccine :syringe: Tag a parent who might find this helpful :thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone::thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone:

EXCERPT: Informed Consent: An Ethical Principle
The National Vaccine Information Center (NVIC) has not advocated for the abolishment of vaccination laws as other groups have proposed. However, we have always endorsed the right to informed consent as an overarching ethical principle in the practice of medicine for which vaccination should be no exception. We maintain this is a responsible and ethically justifiable position to take in light of the fact that vaccination is a medical intervention performed on a healthy person that has the inherent ability to result in the injury or death of that healthy person. .

In consideration of:
the fact that there can be no guarantee that the deliberate introduction of killed or live microorganisms into the body of a healthy person will not compromise the health or cause the death of that person either immediately or in the future; and with very few predictors having been identified by medical science to give advance warning that injury or death may occur; and with no guarantee that the vaccine will indeed protect the person from contracting a disease; and in the absence of adequate scientific knowledge of the way vaccines singly or in combination act in the human body at the cellular and molecular level, vaccination is a medical procedure that could reasonably be termed as experimental each time it is performed on a healthy individual.
.

Further, the FDA, CDC and vaccine makers openly state that often the number of human subjects used in pre-licensing studies are too small to detect rarer adverse events, making post-marketing surveillance of new vaccines a de facto scientific experiment. In this regard, the ethical principle of informed consent to vaccination attains even greater importance." #NVIC #VaccineFreedom #InformedConsent #VaccineChoice #Vaccines #VaccineInjury #VaccineDeath #StopHerdMentality

Abstract: Currently, ethylmercury (EtHg) and adjuvant-Al are the dominating interventional
exposures encountered by fetuses, newborns, and infants due to immunization with
Thimerosal-containing vaccines (TCVS). Despite their long use as active agents of medicines
and fungicides, the safety levels of these substances have never been determined, either for
animals or for adult humans-much less for fetuses, newborns, infants, and children
I reviewed the literature for papers reporting
on outcomes associated with (a) multiple
exposures and metabolism of EtHg and Al during early life, (b) physiological and
metabolic characteristics of newborns, neonates, and infants relevant to xenobiotic
exposure and effects; (c) neurobehavioral, immunological, and inflammatory reactions to
Thimerosal and Al-adjuvants resulting from TCV exposure in infancy. Immunological and
neurobehavioral effects of Thimerosal-EtHg and Al-adjuvants are not extraordinary, rather,
easily detected in high and low income countries, with co-exposure to
methylmercury (MeHg) or other neurotoxicants. Rigorous and replicable studies (in different
animal species) have shown evidence of EtHg and Al toxicities. More research attention has
been given to EtHg and findings have showed a solid link with neurotoxic effects in
humans, however, the potential synergic effect of both toxic agents has not been properly
studied. Therefore, early life exposure to both EtHg and Al deserves due consideration
these effects are

caption:
In 2011 a team of Canadian researchers published a study which linked routine IV fluids with excessive weight loss in newborns. The study concluded that it takes about 24 hours for babies to correct their fluid state and therefore a true birth weight should be done at 24 hours. Here's the issue with with weighing baby at birth with a mother who received IV fluids: those fluids not only over saturate the mother (throwing her into an electrolyte imbalance), but this same thing happens to baby! .
So let's say you had the typical hospital birth..labored for 12 hours with fluids being pumped into you the entire time. Baby is born weighing 8lbs 8oz. You go to your 3 day postpartum checkup and baby is down to 7lbs 5oz! Well..thats over a whole pound lost. The provider you see suddenly encourages you to supplement with formula because your baby is losing too much weight. You wonder how could this be...youve been nursing round the clock, changed plenty of wet diapers. How could this happen? .
You spent months researching breastfeeding and all its benefits for it to come down to this?..and at only 3 days postpartum! You feel like you've failed, but you fear that your baby is starving. So what do you do? You supplement...with formula. Next your milk supply drops because you're not bringing baby to the breast, but rather to the bottle. Before you know it you have an exclusively formula fed baby. .
This scenario is SO common, and I believe receiving IV fluids in labor is a HUGE part of the problem. As if the obstetric community hasn't failed women enough..now their "harmless" interventions caused you to lose all confidence in your ability to feed & nourish your baby from your breasts. .
So what can you do??? 1. STAY OUT OF THE SYSTEM!
2. Say NO to routine IV fluids
3. Bring this study to attention if this happens to you
4. Continue nursing your baby. Bring baby to breast as first solution when she cries
5. Nurse in demand NOT on schedule

caption:
"As the years unfold we begin to understand that we have been introduced to the great truth of pain in childbearing, a pain we naively believed would be confined to labor and delivery, but that visits us at every transition we nurture our children toward: the measured inhale, the steady exhale, the mighty push. And separation. Preschool. Kindergarten. Middle school. High school. College. Career. Marriage. With a familiar aching euphoria, we push them out—from safety and provision to separation and uncertainty. It feels like they would be safer just staying with us, as if safety were the greatest gift we could give them.

Somehow, this painful separation process is for our sanctification as mothers. For years I was not sure what the Bible meant that women would be saved through childbearing, but it grows clearer to me now. I once thought it referred only to giving birth, but its meaning encompasses the span of motherhood. Children are born in an instant, but they are borne across a lifetime. Childbearing saves me because it faithfully (albeit painfully) reminds me over and again that I am weak. It reminds me that I am not self-sufficient, that I do not have what it takes to preserve and protect my children, but that my heavenly Father does. It saves me from the belief that I am God.
Motherhood teaches women the imagery and language of the gospel on an intensely personal level. How appropriate the intertwined imagery of childbirth and the Cross: the necessary spilling of blood for the commencement of life, great loss holding hands with great gain. How appropriate the intertwined language of motherhood and the Great Commission: at the threshold of an unkind world we smile bravely at our children and say “go,” though our hearts may whisper “stay” as the door closes behind them." https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/article/the-truth-about-pain-in-childbearing

Crickets! “To make accurate and ethical public health decisions, the risks of a vaccine must be compared to the risks of the disease one is trying to prevent,” said Dr. Shira Miller, PIC president and founder. “When considering the MMR vaccine to prevent measles, the risks of the MMR vaccine need to be compared to the risks of measles.” There is a five-fold higher risk of seizures from the MMR vaccine than seizures from measles, and a significant portion of MMR-vaccine seizures cause permanent harm. For example, 5% of febrile seizures result in epilepsy, a chronic brain disorder that leads to recurring seizures. Annually, about 300 MMR-vaccine seizures (5% of 5,700) will lead to epilepsy.

Furthermore, the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS), designed to be a warning system for identifying vaccine side effects, receives only about 90 annual reports of MMR-vaccine seizures following the first dose—only 1.6% of the 5,700 MMR-vaccine seizures that actually occur. Thus, other serious vaccine adverse events from MMR, including permanent neurological harm and death, may similarly be underreported. “In the United States, measles is generally a benign, short-term viral infection; 99.99% of measles cases fully recover,” said Dr. Miller. “As it has not been proven that the MMR vaccine is safer than measles, there is insufficient evidence to demonstrate that mandatory measles mass vaccination results in a net public health benefit in the United States.” By JB handley #knowthefacts #thinkbeforeyouvaccinate #vaccineinjury #death #poison

Alongside the benefit to your child of getting vaccinated there is also the benefit of herd/community immunity– but what is it and why is it so important?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
:syringe:What is it? When enough people are vaccinated against an infection its more difficult for it to be spread from person to person as there are less potential people who can be infected.  When you are vaccinated it not only protect you from being infected but also means you cannot pass the infection onto other people. E.g. if someone with measles is surrounded by people who are vaccinated, the disease cannot easily be passed on, and will quickly disappear again. Eventually the disease becomes rare- and sometimes it’s wiped out completely (e.g. small pox).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
:syringe:Why is it important? Unlike vaccination, herd immunity does not give a high level of individual protection, so it is not a good alternative to getting vaccinated. However unfortunately there will always be some children with some severe medical conditions and allergies that can’t have certain vaccines, and therefore rely on herd immunity to protect them. It only takes a small drop in the number of people vaccinated in a population for herd immunity to be less effective and therefore not protect these vulnerable people.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
How many children need to be vaccinated for herd immunity to work? This depends on the germ and how contagious it is. The more contagious the germ, the more people need to be vaccinated for herd immunity to work. Measles is very contagious and needs at least 90-95% of the population to be vaccinated for herd immunity to work. Polio is less contagious and so would require 80-85% of the population to be vaccinated.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
:syringe:Does herd immunity work for all vaccines? No, it is only relevant for disease that are spread directly between people (i.e. are contagious) so it would not work for the tetanus vaccine where the bacteria is caught from bacteria in the environment.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Did you consider herd immunity when getting your kids vaccinated?  A study has shown only 1-6% of parents rank this as their primary reason to vaccinate their kids, whilst over 1/3 say it's the second most important factor.

@Regrann from @_doctor.g_ (defo worth a follow): Forever has medicine been trying to find a "cure" for the common cold not ever realizing that the common cold is the cure. .
.
:small_blue_diamond:Conventional medicine has created a paradigm where they have lost sight of the body's infinite intelligence and instead see it as a machine that needs repair. Most often done by suppressing the symptoms that the body has created to heal itself :man_facepalming_light_skin_tone:. In its simplest form this is most apparent with the common cold.
.
.
:small_blue_diamond:The common cold is not something you "catch" it is something you create, it is your body's adaptation to the conditions and exposures it has been given. In most cases it is poor diet/lack of nutrition, decreased hydration, lack of sun, sleep and exercise, increased physical or mental stress, antibiotic overuse, etc. Resulting in immune suppression and an increase in inherent/exposed bugs that would normally be kept in check.
.

caption:
In California, an underground network of anti-vax doctors will write your children a medical exemption letter to get them out of their #Vaccinations

After an outbreak of measles at Disneyland, California lawmakers had enough and passed SB277, banning kids from attending the state's schools unless they were fully vaccinated, and eliminating the waiver that let parents put their kids and others' in danger by signing a form stating that "immunization is contrary to my beliefs." Since then (thank goodness), the state vaccination rates have soared. But SB277 has a medical exemption clause, which allows parents of children who cannot be vaccinated (for example, children who are immunocompromised) to opt out of the rule.

After the passage of SB277, a new nonprofit called #Physicians for Informed Consent was formed, consisting of "about 200 doctors, scientists, and attorneys who vehemently oppose mandatory vaccine laws," with notorious Orange County vaccine-denier Dr Bob Sears, a pediatrician, as a founding member.

These doctors are writing tons of permanent medical exemption letters for kids of vaccine-denier parents, using scientifically unfounded "genetic tests" and other shaky criteria to help parents continue to deny their kids potentially life-saving treatments. These parents and kids are clustered in charter schools, and in some of those schools in affluent places like Sebastapol, kindergartners have comparable vaccination rates to the poorest children in Haiti.

PIC’s membership is confidential, but its list of founding members and board members is public. I called many of those doctors’ offices and asked what I would need to do to secure a medical exemption. One clinic outside Los Angeles said I would just have to complete a genetic test. When I asked which conditions merited an exemption, some offices said there was a long list of conditions that would qualify; one office assistant said her thyroid problem had secured a medical exemption for her child.

caption:
Gardasil 9 is getting a rap here atm and for no good reason, as per usual.

When experiments are conducted to observe the effects of a new product, typically two groups are compared. One group receives the test product (the test group) and one group receives a placebo (the control group). To observe true differences, the control group should receive an inert substance e.g. a sugar pill or saline. Vaccines are not held to this standard of good science for some reason.

The original Gardasil was trialled on a group that received the vaccine against a group that received a "placebo". However, the placebo was not saline, but aluminium. Aluminium is neurotoxic and stimulates an immune response. The researchers gave these substances to the two groups and then observed reactions. Because the control group was given an active ingredient of the vaccine, their reactions were similar to the test group's. It can thus be concluded that there were no statistical differences between the adverse reactions and ergo the vaccine is safe. There was a very small number of people who actually were given saline but their results were then grouped together with the aluminium "placebo" group and reported as one.

This is obviously misleading because both groups are getting a substance that causes reactions as opposed to one large one getting saline and then their reactions (or lack thereof) being monitored.

Fast forward to Gardasil 9, which was trialled against the original Gardasil for safety :/ since the original Gardasil wasn't tested properly, it's amazing that they can even compare the two or act like the Gardasil 9 is the same when it has more aluminium and more antigens than Gardasil, which is already a dangerous vaccine.

Thousands of young girls and boys have had their lives destroyed by Gardasil - in some cases it is severe but temporary immune system problems and in other cases it is severe and permanent debilitation or death. It is really criminal actually just what is happening with this vaccine.

caption:
Potential Periodontitis Vaccine⠀
⠀
Periodontitis (periodontal disease) is a severe gum infection that can lead to tooth and bone lose. The bacteria that cause this issue are found between the tooth and gum, where they are virtually impossible to remove by regular brushing. They can only be removed professional dental treatment.⠀
⠀
Estimates claim that nearly half of all adults have some form of periodontitis. It grows worse over time and more common in old age. Often the disease goes undetected in its earliest stages.⠀
⠀
The cost of treating periodontal disease is considerable.⠀
Research at the University of Melbourne has developed a vaccine that targets one of the main forms of bacteria behind periodontal disease. Previous vaccines for this bacteria suffered severe limitations, causing the immune system to attack itself. This new vaccine does not suffer this problem. Instead, it target the immune enzymes produced by the bacteria and triggers an appropriate immune response, creating antibodies that neutralize the bacteria toxins.⠀
⠀
Research groups are looking at starting human trials for this new vaccine.⠀
⠀

caption:
If you plug 20 appliances into one outlet and turn them all on at the same time, you're going to blow a circuit. That much load - all at once - is way too much for any electrical system to handle. Can the same situation be happening with today's vaccine schedule?

A June 2016 study by the Journal of American Physicians and Surgeons has concluded that "...infants who receive several vaccines concurrently are significantly more likely to be hospitalized or die when compared with infants who receive fewer vaccines simultaneously." It also goes as far to say that "...multiple vaccines administered during one visit, and vaccinating young infants, significantly increase morbidity and mortality." Apparently, too many shots can blow your baby's circuits. 
Is it a co-incidence the 'electrical' system of the body (the Nerve System) is the one adversely affected when it experiences a vaccine overload? Plus... Whoever in the history of mankind EVER contracted measles, mumps, rubella, diphtheria, pertussis, tetanus, hepatitis B, influenza, polio and chicken pox all at the same time? That would ruin anyone's day... So why does the medical establishment still insist on vaccinating that way?

that science backs them up. This is cherry
picking. The over-all picture needs to be
considered, and the findings combined
demonstrates that potential injury from the
wild disease is overwhelmingly greater than
potential injury from a vaccine.

caption:
I knew better, but I’m still a work in progress.
.
.
The habit of rolling over and checking my phone in the morning is a terrible one. It makes me reactive and lets other people set the tone for the start of my day. That was my morning.
.
.
The vaccine debate rages on, and my heart sank as I read one mother’s comment about wishing people’s children to be inflicted with horrific diseases. I got up, made my coffee, went to my deck, and cried big tears while praying big prayers.
.
.
Are we so disconnected from humanity that we forget we are talking to real mamas with beautiful children and a desire to love them the best way ::they:: know how?
.
.
:heavy_plus_sign: I’ve been the mama with genuine questions who has been silenced.
:heavy_plus_sign: I’ve made well-educated decisions that led to me getting kicked out of doctors offices
:heavy_plus_sign: I’ve cried countless tears over my insecurities as a mother.
:heavy_plus_sign: I’ve been accused of witchcraft, neglect, and stupidity.
.
.
And....
.
.
:heavy_plus_sign: I’ve loved and gently engaged mamas who were too overwhelmed to ask questions, scared to make decisions that go against the norms, cried with them over their own insecurities, and have heard how they have been accused of being “sheep,” neglectful and stupid.
.
.
Friends, it’s easy to forget that people are more than the sum of one post, one opinion and one decision. It’s easy to be arrogant, spiteful and judgmental on social media.
.
.
But women... hear me!!!! We do hard things and we do them well. Loving people with different lifestyles and opinions isn’t always easy, but teaching our children to love well is far more important than what we put in their mouths, where they are birthed or what injections they have or don’t have. That example starts at home. .
.

:smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:
It took a major Ebola epidemic that led to more than 11,000 deaths, but we now finally have a successful Ebola vaccine candidate in development. If approved, the vaccine would vastly reduce the likelihood of ever seeing another major Ebola outbreak. :syringe:
:syringe:
More than a year ago, researchers published striking preliminary results from a large trial on a vaccine called rVSV-ZEBOV in the Lancet. They showed that everyone who got the shot immediately after contact with an Ebola victim didn't get the virus. :syringe:
:syringe:
Today, the same researchers — who hail from the World Health Organization, Guinea’s Ministry of Health, Public Health England, and other international partners — have unveiled their final results in theLancet, and they’re just as remarkable. The vaccine was tested in a trial involving nearly 12,000 people in Guinea and Sierra Leone during 2015 and 2016. Among the 5,837 people who got the vaccine, no Ebola cases were recorded. By comparison, there were 23 Ebola cases in the control group that had not gotten the vaccine. :syringe:
:syringe:
“This trial, confirming the 100 percent efficacy of the rVSV Ebola vaccine, is a simply remarkable outcome,” Dr. Jeremy Farrar, the director of the Wellcome Trust, said of the research. “We’ve shown that by working collaboratively, across international borders and sectors, we can develop and test vaccines rapidly and use them to help bring epidemics to an end.” :syringe:

In 2011 the Swedish music festival ”Peace and Love” booked the Canadian producer Joel Zimmerman, a.k.a. deadmau5. I had never experienced music like his before and to be honest I wasn’t impressed in the beginning. caption:
@Regrann from @lepamperedpig - How did they DO that? How in the hell did they get people to believe that no chemicals are used in organic farming?

What, exactly the benefit of organic ingredients for cosmetics?  The benefit in eating organic is dubious or negligible at best.  Now take that non benefit and go one step further to a topical application- where now you're not consuming it but putting it on an efficient barrier that's designed to keep the good stuff in your body in, and the bad stuff out. 
Most people who buy organic have the mistaken idea that it's pesticide or herbicide free.  Do you think the bugs and weeds only invade conventional crops?  While organic produce doesn't use synthetic pesticides, they do use naturally-derived pesticides and studies have shown that they tend to use more of it to do the same job.  Whatever the origin of the chemicals used on crops, there is a mandated residue limit and tests show it is well below acceptable limits.

caption:
:dashing_away: Microscopic solid or liquid matter suspended in the atmosphere of Earth, particulate matter is one of the many reasons an air filter should be one of your first investments on the road back to health.
-
:factory: The Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) classified particulate matter into ultra-fine (PM-0.1), fine (PM-2.5), and coarse (PM-10) based on its aerodynamic diameter in micrometers, which in turn influences its dissemination in the atmosphere and respiratory penetrance when inhaled by a living organism.
-
:person_getting_haircut: For comparison, the average human hair and particle of fine beach sand have diameters of 70 and 90 micrometers, respectively.
-
:globe_showing_Europe-Africa: Fine particulate matter, which can be either directly released into the air or converted from gaseous precursors, poses monumental risks to health due to its suspension in air for weeks to months and its ability to be transported hundreds or thousands of kilometers.
-
:nose: The nasal cilia and mucus filter coarse particulates, and the coarse particulates that do settle in the trachea or bronchi of the respiratory passages are expelled via sneezing and coughing reflexes.
-
:dashing_away: However, the smaller particulates tend to lodge in the respiratory tract at increased rates, depositing deep within sites of gaseous exchange such as the respiratory bronchioles and the alveoli of the lungs, and ultimately translocate into tissue and circulation.
-
:collision: At a mechanistic level, tissue damage to airways and inflammation can occur due to transition metals present in particulate matter, which induce production of electron-stealing, tissue-damaging reactive oxygen species (ROS).
-
:dna: Similarly, transition metals such as iron elicit genotoxic effects, damaging our DNA.
-
:skull: Disruption of cell membrane integrity is a consequence of the elemental components of particulate matter, which can lead to pulmonary fibrosis.
-
:heart_suit: Particulate matter-mediated induction of pro-inflammatory cytokines, or intercellular signaling molecules which can elicit systemic inflammation, is implicated in cardiovascular disease.
-
:dashing_away: PM-2.5 alters vascular endothelial cells membranes, promoting permeability and consequent development of atherosclerotic lesions.
-
Cont :backhand_index_pointing_down_medium-light_skin_tone:

caption:
#Aluminum can cause neurologic harm.
A study from 30 years ago showed that human adults will increase their urine excretion of aluminum when exposed to higher levels (suggesting adults can clear out excess aluminum).
Adults taking aluminum-containing antacids don’t build up high levels in their body.
There have been reports of infants with healthy #kidneys showing elevated blood levels of aluminum from taking antacids.
The AAP found that people with kidney disease who build up levels of aluminum greater than 100 micrograms per liter in their bloodstream are at risk of #toxicity.
The AAP also states that the toxic threshold may be lower than this.
The paper states that aluminum loading (meaning tissue build up) has been seen even in patients with healthy kidneys who receive IV solutions containing aluminum over extended periods. 
#Aluminum #Alzheimers #Cancer #DrSears #vaccines #vaccineinjury #dementia

It appears Japan may need to take a page from Australia's playbook, for the sake of all pregnant mothers and their unborn children ... "Congenital rubella syndrome
A fetus with a rubella infection may be unaffected or die while in the womb, but many survive with defects in many organs (referred to as congenital rubella syndrome). The most common defects include inadequate growth before birth (growth restriction), small head size, abnormal brain development (causing intellectual disability and abnormal behavior), cataracts, hearing loss, heart defects, and enlargement of the liver and spleen. Some infants have hormone disorders such as diabetes." https://www.merckmanuals.com/home/children-s-health-issues/viral-infections-in-infants-and-children/rubella

@informedconsent
Seqirus Vaccines Limited
BL 2055
Antibody responses were lower in the geriatric population than in younger
subjects. Adverse events occurred less frequently in geriatric subjects (265 years) than in
younger adults. Other reported clinical experience has not identified differences in
responses between the elderly and younger patients. [See ADVERSE REACTION (6)
and CLINICAL STUDIES (14)
DESCRIPTION
FLUVIRIN is a trivalent, sub-unit (purified surface antigen) influenza virus
vaccine prepared from virus propagated in the allantoic cavity of embryonated hens' eggs
inoculated with a specific type of influenza virus suspension containing neomycin and
polymyxin. Each of the influenza virus strains is harvested and clarified separately by
centrifugation and filtration prior to inactivation with betapropiolactone. The inactivated
virus is concentrated and purified by zonal centrifugation. The surface antigens,
hemagglutinin and neuraminidase, are obtained from the influenza virus particle by
further centrifugation in the presence of nonylphenol ethoxylate, a process which
removes most of the internal proteins. The nonylphenol ethoxylate is removed from the
surface antigen preparation.
FLUVIRIN is a homogenized, sterile, slightly opalescent suspension in a
phosphate buffered saline. FLUVIRIN has been standardized according to USPHS
requirements for the 2017-2018 influenza season and is formulated to contain 45 mcg
hemagglutinin (HA) per 0.5 mL dose in the recommended ratio of 15 mcg HA of each of
the following 3 viruses:
A/Singapore/GP1908/2015, IVR-180 (an A/Michigan/45/2015 (HINI)pdm09-like virus;
A/Hong Kong/4801/2014, NYMC X-263B (H3N2) (an A/Hong Kong/4801/2014-like
virus); and B/Brisbane/60/2008, wild type (a B/Brisbane/60/2008-like virus)
The 0.5 mL prefilled syringe presentation is formulated without preservative.
However, thimerosal, a mercury derivative used during manufacturing, is removed by
subsequent purification steps to a trace amount (1 mcg mercury per 0.5 mL dose)
The 5 mL multidose vial formulation contains thimerosal, a mercury derivative,
added as a preservative. Each 0.5 mL dose from the multidose vial contains 25 mcg
mercury
Each dose from the multidose vial or from the prefilled syringe may also contain
residual amounts of egg proteins (1 mcg ovalbumin), polymyxin ( 3.75 meg)
neomycin (2.5 meg), betapropiolactone (not more than 0.5 mcg) and nonylphenol
ethoxylate (not more than 0.015% w/v)

Vaccination is an important tool for decreasing the spread and disease burden of the
widespread bacterial pathogen Streptococcus pneumoniae. However, current vaccines
target only a subset of pneumococcal serotypes, and the nonvaccine types often remain
at high frequencies after vaccination. In some cases, nonvaccine types display a
disconcerting increase in antibiotic resistance frequencies after a population has been
vaccinated by the commonly used PCV7 or PCV13, and the reason for this is unclear

caption:
This mornings cooking batch- our favourite cauliflower, zucchini and leek soup (which Miss wanted to try at 730AM :face_with_tears_of_joy:) and tuna pasta sauce (with spinach, mushrooms and olives) :fish::cucumber::broccoli: HEALTH TIP: there is currently huge concern over the spread of #measles, a #vaccine preventable illness :syringe: Australia is currently at risk of its biggest measles rates in 5 years- we have already had 84 cases this year compared to 103 cases for the whole year of 2018 :face_screaming_in_fear: The measles rise is linked with #travellers who pick up the infection elsewhere (Thailand and Phillipines are current risk areas) and bring it back to Australia- people are contagious before they know they have the disease and rapid spread when they visit public places is what causes the outbreaks. Australians born between 1966 and 1994 MAY have only had 1 of the 2 doses of the measles containing vaccine and so a second dose is available and government funded currently. To those who say “I had measles and it was fine”- it’s certainly not a disease we want to see flare in our community; the thought of Miss S contracting measles scares me hugely- she is vaccinated but it’s certainly not a disease I want her to face. The vulnerable- particularly infants too young to be vaccinated- are most at risk of serious complications including pneumonia and encephalitis (brain inflammation). If you are #travelling, if you’re unsure about your vaccination history, if you know you are not immune but want to be- chat to your GP. At the moment the herd immunity is struggling- :elephant: with less of us #vaccinated diseases like this are more likely to spread. Further post on how early you can vaccinate infants (and when you might want to do this earlier than the schedule) AND an explanation of herd immunity coming in seperate posts :thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone: Tag someone - this is very very serious stuff- the World Health Organisation has said that vaccine hesitancy is a top threat to public health across the globe- this is something we need to talk about :face_with_medical_mask:

caption:
For World Immunization Week (April 24-30) we’d like to recognize the work being done at the Family Immunization Clinic. Canada’s first in-hospital Family Immunization Clinic offers patients, families and visitors at BC Children’s Hospital greater access to publicly-funded immunizations. •
The clinic, which began seeing patients last October, provides flu immunizations at no cost to children, pregnant women, family members and patient visitors. The clinic also offers all publicly-funded immunizations to patients and visitors. The clinic further supports BC Children’s in helping to protect some of the most vulnerable children in our province. •
“We encourage everyone to get vaccinated – especially those who are coming to our hospitals, where patients are at greater risk of flu and its most dire outcomes,” said Dr. Manish Sadarangani, Pediatric Infectious Diseases and Immunology, BC Children’s. •

The clinic has been made possible thanks to a $15 million donation from Lead Benefactor, Save-On-Foods to fund a multi-phase immunization project. In addition to the new clinic, project funding will help improve immunization rates for all children – including those with complex medical conditions – by offering consultation services to physicians across the province, as well as supporting new research. The project will also fund urgently-needed medical equipment in the hospital. •

Learn more about the Family Immunization Clinic at http://www.bcchildrens.ca/our-services/clinics/family-immunization

These two boys had been exposed to the same Smallpox source - one was vaccinated, one was not. The image illustrates the real and enormous difference vaccination makes. Through all of human history, we have eradicated only one disease - Smallpox. In 1801, Edward Jenner hoped his discovery of vaccination would bring nothing less than the annihilation of Smallpox. His hope was realized. On May 24th, 1980, Smallpox was declared eradicated by the World Health Organization.
.
While we won't see this picture today, the unfortunate truth is that even in 2018 we continue to see similar ones with other devastating diseases like Measles and Diphteria... All of which are preventable with one seemingly simple thing: vaccines.
.
#vaccines - they work.
.

.

Myths
Myth: "The flu vaccine can give me the flu"
Fact: Influenza vaccine only contains dead virus and cannot give you influenza.
Myth:"The flu vaccine does not work"
Fact: For most influenza seasons the vaccine provides good protection for 70-90% of
people who get it. For the remainder it can reduce the severity of illness and make
complications from influenza less likely.
Myth: "Side effects from the vaccine are worse than getting the flu"
Fact: Most people do not get any side effects from the vaccine. Side effects, when they
do occur, are usually minor and only last for one or two days, unlike influenza where
symptoms are often severe and can last up to seven days.
Myth: "The flu is not a serious disease"
Fact: Complications from influenza can be life threatening and include pneumonia,

:microbe::microbe::microbe: It’s that time of the year again! Queensland has already hit a 5 year high in its number of cases this summer, with dozens ending up in intensive care. The most effective way to protect yourself and your family is to get VACCINATED. 
Annual vaccination is recommended for ANYONE OVER 6 MONTHS. Some groups of people are eligible for a free flu shot: pregnant women, those with a chronic disease (such as asthma) over 6 months of age, anyone 65 years and older and all Aboriginal and Torres Strait islander people over 6 months of age. 
Even if you have had the flu, vaccination is still important to protect you from other strains. This year, 4 different strains are included in the vaccine. 
Most people will develop immunity within 2-3 weeks of vaccination. Protection from vaccination wanes over time so it is recommended that you get vaccinated prior to the peak of the season (usually around August) in mid-April. Always consider a flu shot if you traveling internationally. 
True influenza is more than a bad cold! Signs and symptoms include: sudden onset of high fever, body aches, extreme fatigue and loss of appetite. Cold symptoms may follow (cough, runny nose, sore throat etc) 
It can last a couple of weeks and really knock you around. ANTIBIOTICS WONT HELP because the flu is a virus (antibiotics only fight bacterial illnesses) Anti-viral medications may be prescribed by your GP in some circumstances which can shorten the duration of your illness. 
Take care of yourself AT HOME if you have the flu. Rest, drink plenty fluids, take paracetamol and nurofen for fever and aches and monitor for complications such as pneumonia and bronchitis .

Just because you’ve never had the flu does not mean you never will! Every year a number of Australians die from influenza so do yourself a favour and get immunised today :flexed_biceps::syringe: :microbe:

caption:
#Italy experienced a threefold increase in cases of #measles over last year.  In response, Italian politicians mandated #vaccination against 12 common infectious diseases, including measles, #polio, #whoopingcough, #meningitis, and hepatitis B, for children through age six, before they can enroll in school. Not to be outdone, #Germany is considering imposing a $2,800 fine against parents who do not allow their children to be vaccinated. 
Fines of up to €2,500 ($2,800) could await parents in Germany who fail to vaccinate their children, as panic and an ongoing outbreak of measles spread like wildfire across the nation.

Last week, a 37-year-old mother of three succumbed to the highly-contagious illness in North Rhine-Westphalia — and that troubling portent has officials rushing to quash the epidemic by requiring kindergartens to inform health authorities if parents do not receive #vaccination counseling.

Noncompliance could find children expelled. “Nobody can be indifferent to the fact that people are still dying of measles,” asserted Germany’s Health Minister Hermann Gröhe, reports Bild, adding the tightening of laws surrounding inoculations will be imperative, due to the widespread outbreak.

In March, the #BBC reported “measles had become endemic (meaning that it is self-sustaining, continuing to spread within the country) in #France, #Germany, Italy, #Poland, #Romania, #Switzerland and #Ukraine,” as Forbes paraphrased. “The worst measles outbreak is in Romania, which reported over 3,400 cases and 17 deaths in just the first 3 months of this year.” By the middle of April, Germany had 504 reported cases of measles in 2017 — up from just 33 in the same time period the previous year, and already in excess of the 326 cases reported for the whole of 2016.

German authorities already have the legal means to fine parents who choose not to vaccinate their children — but reporting those parents had been left to the discretion of schools.

Notes the BBC, the “upper house of the German parliament, the Bundesrat, said forcing kindergartens to report some parents to the health authorities might breach data protection laws.” Continued...

caption:
U.S. #1194
1962 4¢ World United Against Malaria 
Issue Date: March 30, 1962
City: Washington, D.C.
Quantity: 120,155,000
Printed By: Bureau of Engraving and Printing
Printing Method: Giori Press
Perforations:  11
Color: Blue and bister 
U.S. #1194 shows both the Great Seal of the United States, and the emblem of the World Health Organization (a chapter of the United Nations). It commemorates a “World United Against Malaria,” in response to the mosquito-carried infectious disease. Malaria causes fever, convulsions, and joint pain. Victims can enter comas and are in danger of dying. Today, 1 to 3 million people die from malaria each year, and hundreds of millions of people are infected. 
In 1961, in his Inaugural Address, U.S. President John F. Kennedy announced, “Together let us explore the stars, conquer the deserts, and eradicate disease.” It was part of U.S. commitment to worldwide efforts in the 1950s and 1960s to reduce the threat of malaria.

caption:
:warning:Paper dissection: cancer immunoprevention :warning:
____________________________________________
Immune surveillance consists of the elimination of nascent tumors by means of the immune system :crossed_swords:. This process is known to occurs in humans and is key to fight cancer, specially in its first stages :baby_medium-light_skin_tone:.
.
However, despite the efforts of our immune system, cancer is still developing in many people :persevering_face:. This is known as immune editing :heavy_check_mark:: tumor cells expressing highly immunogenic antigents will be recognized and killed by T-cells (see :camera: 2 and 3, explanation below). This favors the selection of low-immunogenic or immune resistant tumor cell variants :flexed_biceps_light_skin_tone:.
.
Protective vaccination in the pre-cancerous stage or in certain risk populations could be key to further boost the immune surveillance to also kill those immune evading cells and ensure the complete elimination of a developing tumor.
.
Currently, only :keycap_3: cancer preventive vaccines :syringe: are available (FDA approved) including :keycap_2: for viral-initiated cancers (cervix cancer caused by human papiloma virus; liver cancer caused by hepatitis virus, [read 1st comment to know why virus can cause cancer]). The third vaccine is against advanced prostate cancer, and should be considered therapeutic and not preventive (Sipuleucel) :face_with_head-bandage:.
.
During the last years,  preventive vaccines have been tested in mice :mouse: without showing autoimmune-related side effects. This vaccines :syringe: have shown increadible results in mice :mouse: and some clinical trials are also showing promising results in humans :breast-feeding_light_skin_tone:.
.
So, the years of cancer immunoprevention have just started and show a bright future for such a common disese :sun_with_face:.
__________________________________________________

"My opposition to new meningitis mandates
for every New York State seventh and twelfth
grader has nothing to do with autism and everything
to do with arithmetic ("Meningitis shot to be rule
for schools," Oct. 28). Meningitis is a rare disease
that affects only 390 people nationally last year.
FDA and industry testing show the meningitis
vaccine to be unusually low efficacy and high risk.
The manufacturers' inserts predict that 1% to 1.3%
of inoculated children will suffer "serious adverse
effects." CDC's Pink Book forecasts that 0.3%
of these will die from the vaccine. Of the 400,000
New York school children inoculated annually,
some 4,000 will become ill and nine will die
in order to prevent around four people from
contracting the disease. At between $84 and $117
per shot, and with the requirement for a two-shot
series, the law is an $80 million annual windfall,
for vaccine manufacturers at taxpayer expense.
This math makes sense only to the pharmaceutical
companies and the Albany politicians who have
taken their money." - Robert F. Kennedy Jr.

Hi friends! Last night, I started a Q&A, on my stories, for friends to post questions they had regarding women’s health and pregnancy. I’ll be doing weekly Q&A’s over @empowering_you just to foster conversations about females, our bodies and overall health. As a future women’s health nurse practitioner, I want to dedicate my life to empowering women to understand their bodies and feel informed about their healthcare decisions. caption:
Keeping pet birds healthy and free of disease

Home improvement products
Many products used for home improvement (e.g., paint, paint remover, paint thinner) emit chemical fumes for many days after being used or installed. Before doing any home improvement projects, remove your birds from your home and don’t bring them back until the products are no longer “out-gassing.” The general rule of thumb is this: If you can smell it, it can harm your bird. 
Metal parts and pieces
Any metal that is small and soft enough to be swallowed can cause life-threatening toxicity to a bird. Carefully check each toy before introducing it to your birds to make sure there are no parts that they might be able to ingest. To avoid zinc, nickel or lead flakes from being ingested by your birds, use medical-grade stainless steel hardware as much as possible in their cages and play areas.

caption:
In the 90s, “polio eradication initiatives” were implemented in India and Africa. The WHO quickly established the same diagnostic changes (explained in the next paragraph) in those nations as were made in the U.S. in 1955. The result, as expected, was the announcement two years ago that India is now polio free. What the WHO so conveniently omitted was any mention of the skyrocketing incidence, in both nations, of acute flaccid paralysis (7) , clinically identical to polio, and following in the wake of the use of the oral polio vaccine, abandoned fifteen years ago in the U.S. because it triggers Vaccine Associated Paralytic Polio
•
In 1960, 6 years after the introduction of the polio vaccine, a community was considered to have a polio epidemic when it had 35 cases of polio per year per 100,000 population. Prior to the introduction of the Salk vaccine, the National Foundation defined an epidemic as 20 or more cases of polio per year per 100,000 population. On this basis there were many epidemics throughout the United States yearly. The present higher rate has resulted in not a real, but a semantic elimination of epidemics. In the decades following the release of the vaccine, additional changes were made to the diagnostic parameters of the disease, changes involving analysis of cerebrospinal fluid and stool and additional testing, each succeeding change making it less and less likely that a diagnosis of paralytic polio would result.

ANTIVAXXER MYTHS DEBUNKED 
7. Good nutrition and hygiene will protect you from most viruses. 
Where the myth comes from: In the 19th century, improved sanitation, nutrition and hygiene went long way toward combatting rampant viruses and bacteria. Some vaccine sceptics have taken this to mean diet and lifestyle are the only defenses we need.
The facts: Polio cases in the U.S. reached a peak in the early 1950s, well after good sanitation and nutrition had become standard—rich and poor children like contracted the illness, which only disappeared in 1979, a generation after the first polio vaccine strategy was introduced in 1955. And even the healthiest diet won't protect you from tetanus or measles.

Cancer, Simian Virus 40 (SV40), and Polio Vaccine Fact Sheet
• SV40 is a virus found in some species of monkey
• SV40 was discovered in 1960. Soon afterward, the virus was found in polio vaccine.
. More than 98 million Americans received one or more doses of polio vaccine from 1955 to
1963 when a proportion of vaccine was contaminated with SV40; it has been estimated that
10-30 million Americans could have received an SV40 contaminated dose of vaccine.
SV40 virus has been found in certain types of cancer in humans, but it has not been
determined that SV40 causes these cancers.

> History of Vaccine Safety
The majority of scientific evidence suggests that SV40 contaminated vaccine did not cause
cancer, however, some research results are conflicting and more studies are needed.
Polio vaccines being used today do not contain SV40. All of the current evidence indicates
that polio vaccines have been free of SV40 since 1963.
Additional Facts
In the 1950s, rhesus monkey kidney cells, which contain SV40 if the animal is infected, were
used in preparing polio vaccines. Because SV40 was not discovered until 1960, no one was
aware in the 1950s that polio vaccine could be contaminated.
SV40 was found in the injected form of the polio vaccine (IPV), not the kind given by mouth
(OPV).
Not all doses of IPV were contaminated. It has been estimated that 10–30 million people
actually received a vaccine that contained SV40.
Some evidence suggests that receipt of SV40 contaminated polio vaccine may increase risk
of cancer. However, the majority of studies done in the US and Europe which compare
persons who received SV40-contaminated polio vaccine with those who did not have shown
no causal relationship between receipt of SV40-contaminated polio vaccine and cancer

caption:
"I'm passionate about the importance of vaccinations during any period of your life including for babies, children, adults and the elderly. During pregnancy is a very important time to ensure that you're vaccinated as well. I am expecting our third baby in July of this year. We are right in the midst of cold and flu season and I am working so hard not to get sick.
.
I am washing my hands, trying to keep my kids away from some of the germs, eating a diet rich in nutrients to boost my immune system, exercising regularly and *trying* to get enough sleep (the last one is so hard for me during pregnancy). A super important way to stay healthy during pregnancy is to make sure that you are up to date on vaccines- particularly the flu shot.
.
I told my OB/GYN that I was going to be writing about pregnancy and vaccines and he was super passionate about it. We spent awhile talking about the importance of vaccines during pregnancy and how the flu shot is such an easy way to prevent the flu which can be deadly to pregnant women and their unborn babies.
.
I got my flu shot either at the end of September or beginning of October. When I went to the doctor to confirm my pregnancy, they asked me right away if I got the flu shot and if I did not, they would have highly recommended it and can give it right there in office." - @minutritionist
.
Congrats to @minutritionist, who is expecting her third bundle of joy! :party_popper:Read her full post by following the link in our profile.

caption:
At the moment lots of councils and maternal child health nurse centres are sending letters to parents in Victoria about a booster dose of the chicken pox containing vaccine (MMRV) as there have been outbreaks recently (lots of them!!). What you need to know- 1 dose of the MMRV (measles, mumps, rubella, varicella- which is chicken pox) is given to all kids on the Australian schedule at 18 months, they get plain MMR at 12 months. The single dose is 85% effective at preventing any case of chicken pox. BUT if you give a second dose then it can be 98% effective at preventing the disease. You can either do a booster at least 4 weeks after your first MMRV dose or get a plain chicken pox vaccine earlier (we can give this from 12 months and can give a vaccine containing only chicken pox and nothing else). If you want to do 2 doses to increase your child's protection you need to pay for the dose NOT on the schedule. Have a chat to your GP if you're interested, tag a mate who might be interested. Why prevent chicken pox? It can be awfully uncomfortable for kids and they get excluded from school/childcare/playgroups until the lesions have dried. PLUS it can have serious complications in severe forms of disease like pneumonia, brain infections and sepsis. Miss S is getting her second booster dose in 3 weeks (she has to wait at least 4 after her 18 month immunisations where she had her first MMRV). Here's me looking all summery today- keep it up Melbourne!! :hugging_face:

caption:
This was me, last Feb w/ the Flu. I was so sick. I worked all day but almost collapsed in the evening before my meeting at the surgery center. I was lucky I had access to great nurses at #90210surgerymedicalcenter who started an IV.
Millions of people get the flu every year and tens of thousands of people die from #flu related causes every flu season. :face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer::face_with_thermometer:
:face_with_medical_mask:Last year, 110 #children died from flu in the US
:face_with_medical_mask:Every year, #influenza #kills between 12,000 and 50,000 people and can send more than 700,000 #people to the hospital.
:face_with_medical_mask:Flu #vaccines cause #antibodies to develop in the body about two weeks after vaccination. :high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage:
:face_with_medical_mask:These #antibodies provide protection against infection with the #viruses that are in the vaccine.
:face_with_medical_mask:Everyone 6 months of age and older should get a flu vaccine every season.
:face_with_medical_mask:Some people who get vaccinated may still get sick. However, vaccination will reduce the severity of illness in people who get vaccinated. :high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage:
:face_with_medical_mask:Flu #vaccination can reduce the risk of flu associated hospitalization for children, working adults, and other adults. :high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage:
:face_with_medical_mask:Vaccination helps protect women during and after pregnancy. :high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage:
:face_with_medical_mask:Getting #vaccinated can also protect a baby after birth from the flu. Mom passes antibodies onto the developing baby during the pregnancy. :high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage::high_voltage:
:face_with_medical_mask:A flu vaccine given during #pregnancy helps protect the baby from flu infection for several months after birth, when he or she is not old enough to be vaccinated. :high_voltage::high_voltage::woman_tipping_hand_medium-light_skin_tone:Protect yourself and your loved ones.
